onal, Inc. (NYSE: GPK), headquartered in Atlanta, Georgia, is a leading provider of packaging solutions for a wide variety of products to food, beverage and other consumer products companies. The Company is one of the largest producers of folding cartons and holds a leading market position in coated-unbleached kraft and coated-recycled board. The Company&#39;s customers include some of the most widely recognized companies in the world.</p><p>Our vision -- to provide packaging solutions that improve the world in which we live -- can be achieved by delivering value to our customers, building a high performance culture for our employees, creating superior returns for our shareholders, and being an environmentally responsible leader in our industry and in the communities in which we operate.</p><p>Graphic Packaging has approximately 13,500 employees working in more than 50 locations in North and South America, Europe, Australia and Asia. We are committed to workplace diversity and offer compensation and benefit programs that are among the best in the industry to reward the talented people who make our company successful. We invite you to review the following employment opportunity and to learn more about us at</p><p>Mission:</p><p>Work closely with Supply Chain and Business Unit leadership and other commodity directors/managers in pursuit of sustainable reductions in the total cost of goods and services procured with simultaneous improvements in the quality and service levels of the supply base.</p><p>Specific Categories: Powered Industrial Vehicles, Equipment Leasing &amp; MRO</p><p>Outcomes:</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Achieve savings targets</p><p>Achieve working capital targets</p><p>Execute SPI strategy in selected commodity category</p><p>Spend compliance with approved suppliers</p><p>Assures security of supply and maintains optimal equipment availability levels.</p><p>Duties and Responsibilities:</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Establish and develop the supply base to ensure availability of quality materials in a timely and cost effective manner.</p><p>Follow the Strategic Procurement Initiative process to drive purchased items towards common specifications and increase supplier competition.</p><p>Prepare manufacturing sites for sourcing events and equipment site visits / audits.</p><p>Develop and maintain a complete list of powered industrial vehicles and associated leases.</p><p>Facilitate timely disposition of equipment that has reached end of useful life or lease life.</p><p>Support the processing and tracking of leases, quotes, agreements etc. in a timely fashion.</p><p>Develop and present on a regular basis fleet cost, performance and aging metrics.</p><p>Review commodity analyst reports for data integrity and validity of assumptions.</p><p>Manage sourcing events to obtain the best unit prices while meeting defined quality and service level parameters.</p><p>Implement Supplier Management Program in selected commodity categories assigned.</p><p>Review contracts and supplier vendor registrations for assigned categories.</p><p>Ensure accurate and timely reporting to Supply Chain finance team regarding SPI and synergy projects, inflationary costs and budget assumptions.</p><p>Effective and frequent communication regarding project updates to Supply Chain management including routine issues impacting the desired project outcomes.</p><p>Support SPI project and procurement strategies and initiatives related to Mill MRO (motors, pumps, machine clothing, pipes, valves and fittings and maintenance services) as directed by the Director Mill MRO</p><p>Carry out all policies and achieve objectives as directed by the Director Mill MRO.</p><p>Manage the efforts of the Lease Analyst provided by our leasing partner.</p><p>Other duties as assigned.</p><p>Other Requirements:</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Bachelorâs degree in packaging, supply chain, operations, engineering, or other related field preferred, or minimum of three (3) years of packaging and or paperboard industry experience in a commodity sourcing role.</p><p>Experience: Minimum of (3) years experience in Procurement, Operations, Technical, Packaging Development in Paperboard / Packaging industries, or as a Financial Analyst supporting Procurement / Supply Chain initiatives.</p><p>Availability to travel to 25%.</p><p>Excellent communications skills (both verbal and written).</p><p>Ability to communicate effectively with all levels of management.</p><p>Must have advanced computer skills including a significant understanding of ERP (e.g., SAP, TM1, and Hyperion) systems.</p><p>Detailed and multi-task oriented.</p><p>Key Competencies:</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Action Oriented</p><p>Integrity and Trust</p><p>Intellectual Horsepower</p><p>Learning on the Fly</p><p>Organizing</p><p>Graphic Packaging is an Equal Opportunity Employer. All candidates will be evaluated on the basis of their qualifications for the job in question. We do not base our employment decision on an employee&#39;s or applicant&#39;s race, color, religion, age, gender or sex (including pregnancy), national origin, ancestry, marital status, sexual orientation, gender identity, genetic identity, genetic information, disability, veteran/military status or any other basis prohibited by local, state, or federal law. Click here to view the EEO is the Law Poster.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Required Skills</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Required Experience</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Position Type: Full Time</p><br /><br /><div style="text-align:left;padding-bottom: 20px;"><a href="/apply-for-job/bjtiaz/commodity-mill-graphic-atlanta-ga-30328" id="ApplyBottomLink" class="bigBlueButtonLink" rel="nofollow" onclick="ga(&#39;send&#39;, &#39;event&#39;, &#39;Links&#39;, &#39;ApplyForJob&#39;, &#39;BottomButton&#39;);">Apply now</a></div></div></div></div><div style="background-color: #fcfcfc; max-width: 400px;" class="sideBar"><div style="text-align:left